            <levelledPara>
                <title>KNOT/KNU Methodology</title>
                <para>
                    The Q100 program uses KNOT (Knowledge Nexus of Tangible-uncertainties) and 
                    KNU (Knowledge Nugget Units) to manage knowledge creation and uncertainty reduction.
                </para>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>What is a KNOT?</title>
                    <para>
                        A KNOT is a cluster of related uncertainties requiring coordinated resolution. 
                        Each KNOT has:
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>Unique ID (e.g., KNOT-00-00-001)</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Residual uncertainty score (0-100, target â‰¤15)</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Set of KNUs for resolution</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>TT token pool for incentivization</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Stakeholder ownership (STK_* roles)</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Example KNOT:</emphasis> KNOT-00-00-001 
                        (Controlled Terminology Foundation) includes 12 KNUs covering glossary 
                        requirements, database schema, term type taxonomy, validation tests, and 
                        usage guides.
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>What is a KNU?</title>
                    <para>
                        A KNU is an atomic unit of knowledge creation work that produces a specific, 
                        verifiable artifact. Each KNU has:
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>Unique ID following pattern: KNU-{ATA}-{SUBSYS}-{SEQ}-{TYPE}-{NUM}</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Type: REQ, SAF, ICD, ANA, TEST, PUB, CM, PLAN</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Status: âšªPLANNED â†’ ðŸ”µGENERATED â†’ ðŸŸ¢APPROVED or ðŸ”´BLOCKED</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Owner (Area of Responsibility)</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Effort estimate (story points)</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>TT token allocation upon completion</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Example KNU:</emphasis> KNU-00-00-001-REQ-001 
                        (Program Glossary Requirements) defines requirements for Q100 terminology 
                        management. Type=REQ, Status=GENERATED, Owner=STK_CM, Effort=8.
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>KNU Lifecycle</title>
                    <para>
                        <sequentialList>
                            <listItem>
                                <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">PLANNED:</emphasis> KNU identified 
                                in KNU_PLAN.csv, not yet started.</para>
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">GENERATED:</emphasis> Artifact 
                                created and committed to repository, awaiting review.</para>
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">APPROVED:</emphasis> Artifact 
                                reviewed, approved, and baselined. TT tokens allocated.</para>
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">BLOCKED:</emphasis> KNU cannot 
                                proceed due to unresolved TBD or missing dependency.</para>
                            </listItem>
                        </sequentialList>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Document Numbering Conventions</title>
                <para>
                    All Q100 documents follow strict naming conventions:
                </para>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>KNU Identifier Format</title>
                    <para>
                        <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
KNU-{ATA}-{SUBSYS}-{SEQ}-{TYPE}-{NUM}

Where:
  ATA     = 2-digit ATA chapter (00-99)
  SUBSYS  = 2-digit subsystem (00-99)
  SEQ     = 3-digit sequence (001-999)
  TYPE    = Artifact type (REQ, ICD, ANA, etc.)
  NUM     = 3-digit artifact number (001-999)

Examples:
  KNU-00-00-001-REQ-001  = General, subsys 00, seq 001, Requirements #001
  KNU-71-00-003-ICD-002  = Power Plant, general, seq 003, ICD #002
  KNU-28-10-001-TEST-001 = Fuel, LHâ‚‚ storage, seq 001, Test #001
                        </verbatimText>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>S1000D DMC Format</title>
                    <para>
                        S1000D Data Module Codes (DMCs) follow S1000D standard:
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
DMC-{MODEL}-{SYSDIFF}-{SYS}-{SUBSYS}-{SUBSUBSYS}{ASSY}-{DISASSY}{VAR}-{INFO}{VAR}-{LOC}_{LEARN}-{EVENT}_{LANG}.{EXT}

Example:
DMC-AMPEL360-00-00-00-00A-042A-A_001-00_EN-US.XML

Where:
  AMPEL360 = Model identifier
  00-00-00-00A = System breakdown
  042A-A = Info code + variant (042 = Usage Guide)
  001-00 = Learn code + event
  EN-US = Language (English-US)
  XML = File format
                        </verbatimText>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>SSOT vs PUB Distinction</title>
                <para>
                    Understanding the difference between SSOT and PUB is critical:
                </para>
                <table>
                    <tgroup cols="3">
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Aspect</entry>
                                <entry>SSOT (Single Source of Truth)</entry>
                                <entry>PUB (Publications)</entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Purpose</entry>
                                <entry>Engineering artifacts, authoritative source</entry>
                                <entry>Derived documentation for end users</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Format</entry>
                                <entry>Markdown, YAML, CSV, JSON</entry>
                                <entry>S1000D XML, PDF, HTML (IETM)</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Lifecycle</entry>
                                <entry>LC01-LC13 categories</entry>
                                <entry>AMM, CMM, IPC, TRN, etc.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Edit Control</entry>
                                <entry>Direct editing by engineers</entry>
                                <entry>Generated from SSOT, manual edits discouraged</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Example</entry>
                                <entry>KNU-28-00-001-REQ-001_fuel-system-requirements.md</entry>
                                <entry>DMC-AMPEL360-28-00-00-00A-001A-A_001-00_EN-US.XML</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Key Rule:</emphasis> SSOT is the authoritative 
                    source. PUB documents are derived via transformation tools or CIR export. 
                    Never manually edit both SSOT and PUB for the same content.
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Repository Navigation Guide</title>
                <para>
                    To find a specific document in the repository:
                </para>
                <para>
                    <sequentialList>
                        <listItem>
                            <para>Identify the OPT-IN axis (O, I, N, T, or P)</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para>Navigate to ATA chapter directory</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para>Choose SSOT or PUB path</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para>For SSOT: Select lifecycle category (LC01-LC13)</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para>For PUB: Select publication type (AMM, CMM, TRN, etc.)</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para>Locate file by KNU ID or DMC</para>
                        </listItem>
                    </sequentialList>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Example Search:</emphasis> Find the fuel cell 
                    requirements document.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
1. Axis: T (Technologies)
2. ATA: 71 (Power Plant)
3. Path: SSOT
4. Lifecycle: LC02 (Requirements)
5. File: KNU-71-00-001-REQ-001_fuel-cell-requirements.md

Full Path:
OPT-IN_FRAMEWORK/T-TECHNOLOGIES.../ATA_71.../SSOT/LC02.../KNU-71-00-001-REQ-001_fuel-cell-requirements.md
                    </verbatimText>
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
